By GARBA MUHAMMAD, Kaduna The list of 17 abducted students of Greenfield University located 34 kilometres along Kaduna – Abuja expressway has been made public. The list was released by a non-academic staff of the university who asked not to be named. He said late Wednesday morning that one of the private security guard of the school was confirmed shot death during the attack by unknown gunmen last night, Tuesday, April 20, 2021. Below is the list of the students – all males – taken away by the gunmen: 1 Abraham Akinje 2 Fortune Alhassan 3 Miracle John 4 Miracle Turman 5 Jesse Jakiri 6 Joseph Davies 7 Abdullahi Yusuf 8 John Yari 9 Michael Samson Ladan 10 Abdulkareem Ibrahim 11 Kabir Hamisu 12 Lemuel Adamu 13 Israel Antonio 14 Israel Musa 15 Nelson David 16 Mariam Nalado 17 Abdulkadir Abubakar The Kaduna State Police Command is yet to comment on the issue. (News Express) KADUNA - Some students have been kidnapped when gunmen attacked Greenfield University on Tuesday evening, the Police command in Kaduna state has confirmed. The university located on Kaduna-Abuja highway, was attacked at about 8:35p.m on Tuesday. ASP Mohammed Jalige, the Command Public Relations Officer, told the News Agency of Nigeria… In "Top Stories" Gunmen have abducted unspecified students of Green Field University along the Kaduna-Abuka Highway in Chikun Local Government Area. The Nation learnt the attack occurred on Tuesday night. Kaduna Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, confirmed the incident. It was learnt gunmen invaded the university and started shooting… In "News" On Sunday night, January 17, gunmen abducted Professor Aliyu Muhammad and killed his teenage son, Abdulaziz Aliyu in Zaria Local Government Area of Kaduna state. Professor Muhammad is the traditional titleholder of Wazirin Wusasa and the Head, Department of Agricultural Protection of the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University (ATBU), Bauchi. PROF… In "News"